<!-- 1. Define Variable -->
// variables :- variables are containers which is used to store infromation
<!--2. Type of Variable -->
 type variable:- Local Variable
                2. Global Variable      
                3. Static variable
  variable Declaration
  In php, variable name begin with $ sign, followed by a name. 
  $roll $class $nmae $email $price

<!-- 3. Rules of variables -->
 // rules 
  1. Variable starts with $ sign.
  2. variable name only starts with a letter, an underscore(-).
  3. Variable name cannot start with  a number.
  4. It is case sensitive which implies that the svariable num in lowercase is different from variable num in uppercase.
  5. Do not use predefined constant name eg. PHP_VERSION, PHP_OS etc.
  6. do not use reserved keywords eg else, if etc.
<!-- 4. Variable Initialization -->
 //variable initialization
  -> PHP cna store all type of data in variables. before using a variable in php, assign a value ti it so Php will create that variable
  store data in it . That means we have to assign data to a variable before attempting to read a variable's value.
  eg :- $nmae = "Unique News";->string value 
  $roll = 111;->int value 
  $price = 2.45;-> flaot value
  <!-- 5. example code -->
  <?php
  $_name ="Example";
  $_roll = 111;
  echo $name,$roll;
  ?>
